{
  "councilId": "law",
  "displayName": "Law & Governance Council",
  "description": "Role-specialized legal reasoning seats. AGI can draft, analyze, compare, simulate, monitor, explain, and audit; humans and lawful institutions keep final authority where rights, liberty, money, immigration, family, property, criminal liability, or public policy are affected. Not legal advice.",
  "humanBoundary": [
    "AGI drafts, analyzes, simulates, and audits; it is not a licensed lawyer, judge, regulator, or public authority.",
    "A licensed human must verify sources, apply professional judgment, manage confidentiality and conflicts, and sign off on legal advice.",
    "Never the final decision-maker on criminal guilt, sentencing, custody, immigration/asylum, detention, constitutional rights, or denial of public services without a lawful human decision and appeal.",
    "Always label output as not legal advice and escalate high-risk matters to a human."
  ],
